  <h2>Weeknight Wellington</h2>
  <p>Weeknight Wellington is a quick and straightforward take on the traditional Beef Wellington that's ideal for hectic weeknights..</p>
  <h2>Ingredients</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Beef fillet or steak</li>
    <li>Puff pastry sheets</li>
    <li>Mushrooms</li>
    <li>Onion, finely chopped</li>
    <li>Garlic</li>
    <li>Fresh thyme</li>
    <li>Salt and pepper to taste</li>
    <li>Olive oil or butte</li>
  </ul>
  <h2>Steps</h2>
  <ol>
    <li> Preheat the oven to the temperature specified by the puff pastry package instructions.</li>
    <li>Season the beef fillet with salt and pepper on all sides.</li>
    <li>n a skillet, heat some olive oil or butter over medium-high heat. Sear the beef fillet on all sides until browned. Remove the fillet from the skillet and set it aside to cool.</li>
    <li>In the same skillet, add a little more oil or butter if needed, then sauté the sliced mushrooms, chopped onion, minced garlic, and fresh thyme until the mushrooms have softened and released their moisture. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Remove from heat and let it cool slightly.</li>
    <li>Roll out the puff pastry sheets on a lightly floured surface. If needed, you can join two sheets together to create a larger piece to wrap the fillet.</li>
    <li>Spread a thin layer of Dijon mustard over the puff pastry sheet(s), leaving a border around the edges.</li>
    <li>Spread the sautéed mushroom mixture evenly over the prosciutto or ham layer</li>
    <li>Place the cooled beef fillet on top of the mushroom mixture</li>
    </ol>